result.name: common-plan-conservation-areas
result.notes: Conservation areas are designations made by local authorities. The boundary of a conservation area defines an area of "special architectural or historic interest" where special requirements placed on local authorities to "preserve or enhance" those areas.

extras.value: Intellectual property rights owned by OS as data has been derived from tracing/snapping to OS Landline Plus/MasterMap; If data is to be published and a charge made for the publication a royalty will have to be paid to Ordnance Survey.; Data cannot be downloaded and then projected on to Google Maps.
